People often ask me,why the black bindi?
Is it your signature look? Is it for fashion or something spiritual?
The answer is simple. It’s for my NANI 🪽

I spent my whole childhood with her. I lived with her, laughed with her, and learned from her. The bond we shared was something else.
For me, it has always been my nani first, then my mom, that’s how close we were.

A few days after she left us, we were going through her things and found a bag of black bindis. the ones she wore every single day. It was her thing. “HER SIGNATURE LOOK”
And somehow, without planning it, it became part of me too.

And the more I grow, the more I realize, I’m more like her than I am like my mom.
My nani was fiercely independent. She used to travel state to state playing badminton, back in a time when girls were married off young and weren’t allowed to go anywhere on their own.
She broke norms with grace and courage.
And in so many ways, I see that spirit in myself now too.

Now when I wear a black bindi, I don’t do it to make a statement. I do it to feel close to her.
It’s a little piece of her I carry with me.
And every time I put it on… I feel like she’s still with me🤍
